

# Commands
npm create vite@latest

enter yes

provide a client name

Select React as the frame work

select Typescript + SWC as the variant 

npm run dev

## Reference 
https://vite.dev/guide/ 

---

* When we use npm run dev, it takes a look inside the ``vite.config.ts file for its configuration.

* Updated port the client should list on in the config file with the following:

````

export default defineConfig({
  server: {
    port:3000
  },
  plugins: [react()],
})
````

* In the package.json file check if the latest version of react is being used. Hover of the  default version provided